(339, 162, '__links', 'field_64dd1a2199239'),
(340, 162, '_solution', '<p>By experimenting with various subject lines, you can improve your email marketing campaigns. Each test provides valuable insights and enables you to refine your strategy for better engagement with your audience.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Step-by-step Guide</h5>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">1</span> For this task, you will create a new email and on the <strong>Basic Email Information</strong> window, scroll down to the <strong>A/B Test</strong> section and click on <strong>Enable A/B Testing</strong>. Enabling A/B testing will generate A and B versions of the email.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/day-6-ab-testing.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/day-6-ab-testing.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">2</span> Next, update the email copy and subject lines for each email by navigating between tabs A and B. Since you want to improve the open rates, you will only be testing the subject lines for this task.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/day-6-ab-email.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/day-6-ab-email.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">3</span> In the final step, you need to configure your A/B test. Click on the <strong>Sending</strong> tab and scroll down to the <strong>A/B Test</strong> section. There are three settings that need to be configured:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>How long do you want the test to run before a winner is selected? You can keep it as 1 day.</li>\r\n<li>What criteria do you want to use to determine the winner? Select Opens since we are testing subject lines.</li>\r\n<li>What percentage of your audience do you want to use for testing? You can keep it at 25%.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/day-6-ab-config.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/day-6-ab-config.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">4</span> Once you have completed the A/B Test configuration and selected the distribution list of trade-show attendees, the email is ready to be scheduled.</p>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"78\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n'),
