(359, 163, '_solution', '<p>Tracking web visit activity provides valuable information about potential prospects. Account Engagement collects web activity data through website tracking code. The platform tracks visitors even before they become known prospects and combines all data when a prospect completes an Account Engagement form. This, in return, provides insight into the prospect\'s past and current website behavior.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Step-by-step Guide</h5>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">1</span> First, you will create a page action that triggers a completion action when a prospect visits the product launch event page. To do this, you need to know the URL of the landing page for the product launch event. Follow the steps below to create your first page action. In the <strong>Page URL</strong> field, enter the exact URL of the event page. You can use either the default Account Engagement URL or the vanity URL that you have selected.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/page-action.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/page-action.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"223\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">2</span> Next, you will add a completion action to the page action that will notify the prospect owner when their prospect visits the event page. To do this, select <strong>Notify Assigned User</strong> from the Action dropdown menu. </p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/page-action-2-1.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/page-action-2-1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">3</span> Once you create a page action, it will automatically become active and triggers <strong>once per hour</strong> whenever prospects visit the page.</p>'),
