(597, 362, '_solution', '<p>In this example, the AttributeValue function is used to retrieve the subscriberâs first name from a sendable data extension. The retrieved first name is then passed as an argument to the ProperCase function to return the name with the first letter capitalised. The result is stored in a variable @firstName, which is then used in the email to greet the recipient with a personalised greeting containing their first name.</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n<code class=\"language-html\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\">%%[\r\nVAR @firstName\r\nSET @firstName = AttributeValue(\"FirstName\")\r\nSET @firstName = ProperCase(@firstName)\r\n]%%\r\n\r\nHello %%=v(@firstName)=%%,\r\n\r\nWe are excited to announce our new holiday package that is perfect for a getaway. &lt;a href=\"https://www.testlink.com\">Test &lt;/a> With stunning beaches and breathtaking views, this package will make your vacation unforgettable.\r\n\r\nThank you for choosing us as your travel partner.\r\n\r\nBest regards,\r\nThe Travel Company</code>\r\n</pre>'),
