(658, 378, '_solution', '<p>Sending a personalized invite to senior executives not only makes them feel valued but also significantly increases the chances of their attendance. By creating a dynamic list, you can target the right audience for this exclusive invitation. Additionally, the email uses Handlebars Merge Language (HML) to ensure that the email has an appropriate salutation.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Step-by-step Guide</h5>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">1</span> Let\'s begin by creating a dynamic list. If you have reviewed the database, you\'ll notice a common pattern: all C-level titles include the word \"Chief\" in their titles, while VP-level executives have titles that begin with \"VP of...\". By using these criteria, you can construct your dynamic list for the email.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/day-9-1-dynamic-list.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/day-9-1-dynamic-list.png\" alt=\"Dynamic List Creation\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"120\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">2</span> Next, create a draft email to invite senior executives to the event. You can either write your own email or use the template provided in the resources section.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">3</span> Lastly, one of the requirements is to ensure that no email is sent without a salutation. If a person\'s first name is missing, a default value should be displayed. To achieve this, you will leverage Handlebars Merge Language (HML). Here is the HML code that you can use. If the recipient\'s first name is missing, it will display \"Customer\".:</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code class=\"language-html\">{{#if Recipient.FirstName}}{{Recipient.FirstName}}{{else}}Customer{{/if}},</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">4</span> Once you have previewed the email and are satisfied with the dynamic list, the email is good to go.</p>'),
