(720, 392, '_solution', '<p>Engaging with prospects through Engagement Studio is a powerful nurturing strategy. This approach provides personalized interactions that guide your attendees towards loyalty and conversion.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Step-by-step Guide</h5>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">1</span> To start, create three email templates. These templates will be used in the Engagement Studio program and sent to the attendees of the product launch event. After creating the template, check the Engagement Program Emails option to make the email templates visible in the Engagement Studio program.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-11-esp-template.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-11-esp-template.png\" alt=\"Email Template Creation\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"59\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">2</span> Next, prepare an audience list for the Engagement Studio program. This can be a dynamic list based on Salesforce campaign membership* or a static list created from the product launch event attendees imported into Account Engagement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Note: Salesforce campaign membership will be covered in upcoming challenges.</p>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"37\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">3</span> As the final step, you will create and publish an Engagement Studio Program. You will use the audience list that you create above as the Recipient List, and add three Send Email actions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These emails will be sent every Tuesday for a duration of 3 weeks. A prospect will continue receiving emails unless they are assigned. To support this logic, we will add three Rule nodes before each email send activity, and set the rule to check the prospect\'s assignment status. If the prospect is assigned, they will exit the program.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your program setup may look similar to the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-11-esp-flow.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-11-esp-flow.png\" alt=\"Engagement Studio Program Flow\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">4</span> To review the program\'s steps, visit the Test tab. Once satisfied with the flow, click <strong>Start</strong> to launch the program.</p>\r\n'),
