(749, 398, '_solution', '<p>Congratulations on exploring the Einstein features available to you in Account Engagement and creating a dynamic list that utilizes the Einstein Engagement Frequency. If you encounter any challenges with your solution, refer to the step-by-step solution guide provided below.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Step-by-step Guide</h5>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">1</span> Begin by creating a dynamic list to segment your target prospects. Set the criteria for <strong>Einstein Engagement Frequency</strong> to equal <strong>On Target</strong>. Running this dynamic list will yield prospects most likely to engage with your next email.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-12-eff.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-12-eff.png\" alt=\"Dynamic List Creation\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"120\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">2</span> Next, create and schedule your email, selecting the dynamic list you just created. This simplifies reaching the most engaged segments using <strong>Einstein Engagement Frequency</strong>, eliminating the need for complex rules in Account Engagement.</p>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"78\" status=\"closed\"]'),
