(1021, 460, '_solution', '<p>Multivariate Testing is an often overlooked feature with significant potential for improving the conversion rates of your landing page. By enabling Multivariate Testing, the platform can automatically distribute traffic to different landing pages, allowing for data-driven decision-making that can greatly enhance the performance of your landing pages.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Step-by-step Guide</h5>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">1</span> For this challenge, the team was interested in evaluating the performance of the landing page when the form was placed above the fold. To create your second landing page, you can utilize the new layout template. Once you have published the landing page, proceed to create a Multivariate test. On the configuration page, you can adjust the traffic allocation between the different landing pages.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-19-lp-test.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-19-lp-test.png\" alt=\"Landing Page Test Setup\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"468\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">2</span> After publishing the multivariate test, you need to provide a new URL to all stakeholders that promotes the research paper. To assess the performance of the landing page, you can checkout the Multivariate Tests page. MCAE will automatically display the top-performing landing page based on form submissions for each landing page.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-19-lp-report.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-19-lp-report.png\" alt=\"Landing Page Report\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n'),
