(1103, 486, '_solution', '<p>Automating the process of adding prospects to a Salesforce campaign when they download an asset is an efficient way to track prospect engagement across multiple campaigns. It saves time and provides real-time data on campaign engagement, which helps in making better decisions. </p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Step-by-step Guide</h5>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">1</span> For today\'s task, you will use completion actions on forms. However, before adding leads and contacts to a campaign, you need to have a campaign created in Salesforce. Go to <strong>Salesforce Campaigns</strong> and ensure that you have a campaign specifically created for the research paper. If you don\'t have a campaign yet, please create one.</p>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"487\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">2</span> Open the research paper form and go to the Completion Actions tab. Scroll down to the Completion Actions section and click on <strong>+ Add Action</strong>. Choose <strong>Add to Campaign</strong> and locate the corresponding Salesforce Campaign. In the Campaign Member Status field, select Responded.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-21-salesforce-campaign.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-21-salesforce-campaign.png\" alt=\"Salesforce Campaign Setup\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">3</span> With this automation in place, whenever prospects download the research paper, they will be automatically added to the Salesforce campaign. This provides the marketing team with excellent visibility into the performance of marketing assets and enables them to measure ROI.</p>'),
