(1146, 502, '_solution', '<p>Creating an Engagement Studio program to nurture prospects who are not yet ready to make a purchase can help keep their interest and guide them towards making a buying decision. By designing your program, you can ensure that your messaging is customized to their specific stage in the buying process.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Step-by-step Guide</h5>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">1</span> Engagement Studio programs consist of two primary elements: <em>recipient lists</em> and <em>email templates</em>. You can also configure suppression lists, program paths, and even re-entry criteria.</p>\r\n<p>In today\'s challenge, your first task is to create a dynamic list that captures prospects who have not yet reached <strong>30 points</strong> and have not been assigned. It is important to check the assignment status to avoid sending emails to prospects who are already being engaged by your Sales team. The recipient list for this program will follow a simple logic: the prospect\'s assignment status must be <strong>not assigned</strong> and their prospect score must be less than <strong>30</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-22-dynamic-list.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-22-dynamic-list.png\" alt=\"Dynamic List Creation\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"120\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">2</span> The second step is to set up the Engagement Studio program. Your program will have a simple logic. Each prospect will receive one email per week for three weeks. After three weeks, prospects will exit the journey if they have not reached <strong>30 points</strong>. If you would like to stay in the nurture program and receive promotions for new resources as they become available, you can add a tag and set a wait time of 365 days. Any prospects that reach <strong>the Tag step</strong> will wait for 365 days before exiting the program.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-22-nurture-wait.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-22-nurture-wait.png\" alt=\"Nurture Program Setup\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"494\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">3</span> Today, you learned about the important part of a Lead Lifecycle program. It focuses on nurturing people who are interested in buying but not quite ready yet. This step is crucial for converting potential prospects into actual customers.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n'),
