(1181, 506, '_solution', '<p>Creating a process to find inactive leads gives you a chance to tidy up your database and rethink your strategies for engaging with customers. By removing inactive leads, you can also make sure that your account stays within the database limit.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Step-by-step Guide</h5>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">1</span> The process of cleaning up your database begins by creating a dynamic list to identify inactive prospects. There are several ways to set up this dynamic list. For today\'s challenge, you will focus on unassigned prospects who have not synchronized with Salesforce. Specifically, you will target unassigned prospects who have been inactive in Account Engagement for the past 180 days.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-23-dynamic-list.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-23-dynamic-list.png\" alt=\"Dynamic List for Inactive Prospects\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"120\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">2</span> Once your new dynamic list is populated, review a few records manually to ensure they meet your criteria and are actual prospects that you want to remove from your database. From the dynamic list view, select all the records in the table and choose \"Delete\" from the dropdown menu in the bottom left corner of the table.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-23-delete-records.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-23-delete-records.png\" alt=\"Deleting Records from Dynamic List\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">3</span> When it comes to cleaning up your database, Account Engagement offers a unique capability that may not be found in other marketing automation platforms. When you delete a record in Account Engagement, it is sent to the recycle bin. The deleted prospects in the recycle bin do not count toward usage limits and will be automatically restored if a prospect engages with your content, such as by submitting a form.</p>'),
