(1200, 509, '_solution', '<p>A preference center is a helpful tool that provides useful information about your customer\'s preferences. This helps in tailoring communications and creating personalized experiences, which are important in today\'s customer-focused marketing world.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Step-by-step Guide</h5>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">1</span> Every preference center requires options or public lists where your customers can sign up. The process for creating a public list in Account Engagement is similar. To create a public list, follow the same steps as when creating a standard list, but make sure to select the <strong>Public List</strong> checkbox to make it visible on the preference center.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For todayâs challenge, after creating your first list, repeat the same steps for other public lists: Monthly Newsletter, Events and Webinars, Product Updates, Data Management Solution, and Data Analytics Solution.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-24-public-list.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-24-public-list.png\" alt=\"Creating Public List\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">2</span> To create a new customer preference center, navigate to Account Engagement Email > Preference Pages and click on <strong>+ Add Email Preferences Page</strong>. In the new preference page, add the lists you created in Step 1 under the Associated Lists section. These lists will be displayed on the new preference center. You can also set up a user vanity URL. Additionally, you have the option to update the form content and the thank you message that appears after form submission. Make sure to set the Layout Template that you have imported from the resource section on the right.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-24-preference-center.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-24-preference-center.png\" alt=\"Setting Up Preference Center\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">3</span> The final step is to add the new preference link to your emails. You can do this by clicking on the link in the email and locating your new preference center under the <strong>Link Type: Email Preference Page</strong> option.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-24-email-preference-center.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-24-email-preference-center.png\" alt=\"Adding Preference Link to Email\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n'),
