(1252, 518, '_solution', '<p>Properly handling data consent is crucial for maintaining trust with your prospects and ensuring compliance. Implementing a system to regularly reconfirm consent is a way to ensure that your communication efforts are appreciated and effective.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Step-by-step Guide</h5>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">1</span> To complete today\'s challenge, you need to create multiple assets:</p>\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>A custom field for capturing the consent date.</li>\r\n        <li>A landing page with a form.</li>\r\n        <li>Two email templates.</li>\r\n        <li>A dynamic list.</li>\r\n        <li>An Engagement Studio Program.</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    <p>First, let\'s create a custom field to capture the consent date. This field will also be used to update the consent data for existing prospects when importing the sample dataset.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-26-consent-date.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-26-consent-date.png\" alt=\"Creating Consent Date Custom Field\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"114\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">2</span> Next, create a simple form with an email field. Upon form submission, set the form completion action to update the <strong>Consent Date</strong> field with <strong>today\'s date</strong>. After that, create a new landing page and add the form to the landing page.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-26-form.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-26-form.png\" alt=\"Creating Form\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"95\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">3</span> Then, create two email templates: one as the initial email and another as a reminder to prospects whose consent date was 180 days ago. You can use the email template provided in the resources section for the emails. You also need to create a recipient list, which consists of prospects who should receive the consent emails.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-26-dynamic-list.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-26-dynamic-list.png\" alt=\"Creating Dynamic List\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"120\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">4</span> Finally, create the Engagement Studio program. The program starts by sending an initial email. A rule is then added to check after 7 days if the consent date has been updated. If the consent is still older than 180 days, a final reminder email is sent. If the individual has not completed the form and their consent is still older than 180 days, the program will remove the consent data.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-26-engagemanet-studio.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-26-engagemanet-studio.png\" alt=\"Engagement Studio Program Setup\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n'),
