(1636, 663, '_solution', '<p>To successfully complete today\'s challenge, it is important to understand comparison operators that allow you to compare different values based on the conditions you define. In the challenge below, you will use these operators in the <code>WHERE</code> clause to retrieve data that meets a specified condition.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Today, you will learn about the <code>WHERE</code> clause with the <code>!=</code> operator. This operator allows you to apply a specific condition to filter out your results.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n<code class=\"language-sql\">\r\nSELECT\r\n    id,\r\n    internet_package\r\nFROM [NextMobile Packages]\r\nWHERE\r\n    internet_package != \'Gigabit Fibe 1.5\'\r\n</code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n<h5 class=\"mt-4\">SQL Queries and Operators Used</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><code>SELECT</code>: Specifies which columns you want to show in your results.</li>\r\n    <li><code>FROM</code>: Indicates the table from which you\'re extracting the data.</li>\r\n    <li><code>WHERE</code>: Enables filtering of the data based on specific conditions.</li>\r\n    <li><code>!=</code>: The Not Equal operator to exclude rows that match a specific text value.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<aside class=\"bg-light-subtle p-4 my-3 rounded-3 border border-light-subtle\" role=\"alert\">\r\n    â¡ï¸ Query Result: <strong>703</strong>\r\n</aside>\r\n\r\n<p>You have just executed a precise query that is important for targeted communications in the marketing world. Your SQL skills are improving with each passing day. Are you ready for Day 3? I certainly am!</p>\r\n'),
