(1839, 678, '_solution', '<p>Today\'s objective is to go beyond basic data retrieval and focus on synthesizing and interpreting information. Utilizing the <code>COUNT</code> and <code>SUM</code> functions, your task is to generate a report that effectively categorizes orders based on their status. This report will provide valuable insights into the volume and value of each category, enabling us to better understand our data.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n<code class=\"language-sql\">\r\nSELECT \r\n    status,\r\n    COUNT(amount),\r\n    SUM(amount)\r\nFROM [NextMobile Orders_2023]\r\nGROUP BY\r\n    status\r\n</code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n<h5 class=\"mt-4\">SQL Queries and Operators Used</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><code>SELECT</code>: Choose the columns and aggregate functions for output.</li>\r\n    <li><code>FROM</code>: Point to the table containing the data.</li>\r\n    <li><code>COUNT</code>: A function used to tally the number of records.</li>\r\n    <li><code>SUM</code>: Calculate the total sum of a numeric column.</li>\r\n    <li><code>GROUP BY</code>: Organize the data into groups based on one or more columns.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<aside class=\"bg-light-subtle p-4 my-3 rounded-3 border border-light-subtle\" role=\"alert\">\r\n    ð¡ <strong>Query Result:</strong> Status, Count, Sum\r\n    <ul class=\"mb-0\">\r\n	  	<li>delayed, 21, 125911.60</li>\r\n		<li>onhold, 32, 180829.59</li>\r\n	  	<li>cancelled, 139, 732426.00</li>\r\n	  	<li>shipped, 808, 4195322.57</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n</aside>\r\n\r\n<p>Your progress in SQL is shaping you into a valuable asset. Keep up the great work and stay tuned for more challenges!</p>\r\n'),
