(1858, 679, '_solution', '<p>Today, you can identify unique addresses with the precision of SQL. By using the <code>DISTINCT</code> keyword in combination with <code>CONCAT_WS</code>, you can create a unique identifier for each household. This ensures that you do not assign multiple vouchers.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n<code class=\"language-sql\">\r\nSELECT \r\n    DISTINCT CONCAT_WS(\',\', address, city, state, postal_code, country)\r\nFROM [NextMobile Users]\r\n</code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n<h5 class=\"mt-4\">SQL Queries and Operators Used</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><code>SELECT</code>: Specify columns for output, in this case, unique address combinations.</li>\r\n    <li><code>DISTINCT</code>: Fetch unique values, crucial for preventing voucher duplication.</li>\r\n    <li><code>CONCAT_WS</code>: Adds two or more expressions together with a separator.</li>\r\n    <li><code>FROM</code>: Indicate the table containing the data.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<aside class=\"bg-light-subtle p-4 my-3 rounded-3 border border-light-subtle\" role=\"alert\">\r\n    ð¡ <strong>Query Result:</strong> 812 rows\r\n</aside>\r\n\r\n<p>Great job! You are playing a vital role in ensuring the success of NextMobile\'s customer appreciation event. Your attention to detail when working with data ensures a fair and efficient distribution process. Keep up the good work and continue to explore and master SQL!</p>\r\n'),
