(2027, 704, '_solution', '<p>Welcome to Day 16! Today, you will focus on analyzing the monthly order amounts to determine the minimum and maximum orders. This analysis is essential for NextMobile\'s marketing strategies as it allows us to customize our campaign planning based on customer spending behaviors.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n<code class=\"language-sql\">\r\nSELECT \r\n    MONTH(date), \r\n    MIN(amount) AS MinOrder, \r\n    MAX(amount) AS MaxOrder\r\nFROM [NextMobile Orders_2023]\r\nWHERE status = \'shipped\'\r\nGROUP BY MONTH(date)\r\n</code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n<h5 class=\"mt-4\">SQL Queries and Functions Used</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><code>SELECT</code>: Specifies the columns or calculated metrics to display in the output.</li>\r\n    <li><code>MONTH</code>: Extracts the month from the date column, facilitating the grouping by month.</li>\r\n    <li><code>MIN</code>: Calculates the lowest order amount for each month, labeled for clarity.</li>\r\n    <li><code>MAX</code>: Determines the highest order amount for each month, providing insight into the range of customer spending.</li>\r\n    <li><code>FROM</code>: Indicates the table containing the order data for the year 2023.</li>\r\n    <li><code>WHERE</code>: Filters the orders to include only those that have been shipped, ensuring the analysis is based on completed transactions.</li>\r\n    <li><code>GROUP BY</code>: Organizes the results by month, allowing for a clear monthly comparison of order amounts.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h5>ð¡ Output</h5>\r\n<aside class=\"bg-light-subtle p-4 my-3 rounded-3 border border-light-subtle\" role=\"alert\">\r\n    <table class=\"table\">\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>MONTH</th>\r\n            <th>MinOrder</th>\r\n            <th>MaxOrder</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>9</td>\r\n            <td>215.22</td>\r\n            <td>9958.1</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>3</td>\r\n            <td>255.46</td>\r\n            <td>9780.18</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>12</td>\r\n            <td>206.68</td>\r\n            <td>9981.16</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>6</td>\r\n            <td>314.19</td>\r\n            <td>9972.7</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>7</td>\r\n            <td>175.59</td>\r\n            <td>9998.48</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>1</td>\r\n            <td>224.66</td>\r\n            <td>9460.54</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>10</td>\r\n            <td>268.64</td>\r\n            <td>9955.34</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>4</td>\r\n            <td>304.17</td>\r\n            <td>9932.25</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>5</td>\r\n            <td>283.54</td>\r\n            <td>9936.44</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>2</td>\r\n            <td>509.69</td>\r\n            <td>9981.05</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>11</td>\r\n            <td>415.42</td>\r\n            <td>9955.63</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>8</td>\r\n            <td>235.1</td>\r\n            <td>9875.82</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </table>\r\n</aside>\r\n\r\n<p>Great job! Your analysis not only shows the monthly order trends but also helps find opportunities for targeted marketing campaigns. Your improving SQL skills are making a real difference in NextMobile\'s marketing accuracy. Keep expanding your knowledge as we tackle more challenges!</p>\r\n'),
