(2084, 707, '_solution', '<p>Welcome to Day 19\'s solution guide! You\'ll be leveraging SQL\'s <code>DATEPART</code> function to break down sales into quarters and the <code>SUM</code> function to tally up total sales per quarter. This way, we\'ll get a comprehensive overview of the yearly performance.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n<code class=\"language-sql\">\r\nSELECT \r\n    DATEPART(quarter, date) AS quarter,\r\n    SUM(amount) AS total_sales\r\nFROM [NextMobile Orders_2023]\r\nWHERE status = \'shipped\'\r\nGROUP BY DATEPART(quarter, date)\r\n</code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n<h5 class=\"mt-4\">SQL Queries and Functions Used</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><code>SELECT</code>: Chooses columns or derived columns for output.</li>\r\n    <li><code>FROM</code>: Specifies the relevant table.</li>\r\n    <li><code>WHERE</code>: Filters data using conditions.</li>\r\n    <li><code>DATEPART</code>: Extracts a specific part of a date (in this case, the quarter).</li>\r\n    <li><code>SUM</code>: Calculates the total of a numeric column.</li>\r\n    <li><code>GROUP BY</code>: Groups rows together based on a common column value.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<aside class=\"bg-light-subtle p-4 my-3 rounded-3 border border-light-subtle\" role=\"alert\">\r\n    ð¡ <strong>Query Result</strong>\r\n    <table class=\"table\">\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>quarter</th>\r\n            <th>total_sales</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>3</td>\r\n            <td>1103381.45</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>1</td>\r\n            <td>1047334.08</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>4</td>\r\n            <td>1013364.33</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>2</td>\r\n            <td>1031242.71</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </table>\r\n</aside>\r\n\r\n<p>By analyzing sales data using SQL, you\'ve provided NextMobile with valuable insight for next year\'s plans. SQL\'s date functions, which allow segmentation by week, month, quarter, and year, are incredibly useful.</p>\r\n'),
