(2240, 716, '_solution', '<p>Marketing Cloud provides a variety of data views that offer valuable insights into subscriber behavior. Utilizing these views can deepen your understanding of email marketing performance, enabling you to make data-driven decisions to enhance engagement.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n<code class=\"language-sql\">\r\nSELECT \r\n    id,\r\n    email,\r\n    o.eventdate AS opened,\r\n    c.eventdate AS clicked\r\nFROM [NextMobile Users] u\r\nLEFT JOIN\r\n    [NextMobile Open] o\r\nON\r\n    o.subscriberkey = u.id\r\nLEFT JOIN\r\n    [NextMobile Click] c\r\nON\r\n    c.jobid = o.jobid AND c.subscriberkey = o.subscriberkey\r\nWHERE\r\n  o.jobid = \'765452\' OR o.jobid IS NULL\r\n</code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n<h5 class=\"mt-4\">SQL Queries and Functions Used</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><code>SELECT</code>: Retrieves specific columns (id, email, opened, clicked).</li>\r\n    <li><code>FROM</code>: Specifies the data source (NextMobile Users table).</li>\r\n    <li><code>LEFT JOIN [NextMobile Open] o</code>: This joins the open data with user data, ensuring all customers are included in the analysis, even those without an open event.</li>\r\n    <li><code>LEFT JOIN [NextMobile Click] c</code>: This join combines data from NextMobile Open and NextMobile Click, matching on SubscriberKey and JobID.</li>\r\n    <li><code>WHERE</code>: The filter applied ensures that only the interactions related to the specific job ID of the transactional email are considered.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<aside class=\"bg-light-subtle p-4 my-3 rounded-3 border border-light-subtle\" role=\"alert\">\r\n    ð¡ <strong>Query Result</strong>: 943\r\n</aside>\r\n\r\n<p>This analysis will help the marketing team understand who\'s engaging with their emails, empowering them to tailor future communications. There are just a few days left in SQL30, so keep up the fantastic work!</p>\r\n'),
