(2259, 717, '_solution', '<p>Marketing Cloud\'s Bounce Data view holds a wealth of insights into your email deliverability health. By analyzing this data, you can identify potential issues that might be hindering the success of your email campaigns. Let\'s use the provided SQL query to investigate the NextMobile team\'s bounced emails.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n<code class=\"language-sql\">\r\nSELECT\r\n    COUNT(subscriberkey),\r\n    domain,\r\n    LEFT(SMTPBounceReason,100) AS BounceReason\r\nFROM\r\n    [NextMobile Bounce]\r\nWHERE\r\n    eventdate BETWEEN \'2024-02-01\' AND \'2024-02-29\'\r\nGROUP BY\r\n    domain,\r\n    LEFT(SMTPBounceReason,100)\r\nHAVING\r\n    COUNT(subscriberkey) > 1\r\n</code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n<h5 class=\"mt-4\">SQL Queries and Functions Used</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><code>SELECT</code>: Retrieves specific columns (subscriber count, domain, bounce reason).</li>\r\n    <li><code>LEFT</code>: Used to truncate the <code>SMTPBounceReason</code> to the first 100 characters.</li>\r\n    <li><code>FROM</code>: Specifies the data source (NextMobile Bounce data view).</li>\r\n    <li><code>WHERE</code>: Filters the data to include only bounce events in February 2024.</li>\r\n    <li><code>GROUP BY</code>: Groups the data by domain and bounce reason.</li>\r\n    <li><code>HAVING</code>: Filters groups to include only those with two or more subscribers bounced.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<aside>\r\nð¡ <strong>Query Result:</strong> 71\r\n</aside>\r\n\r\n<p>Analyzing bounce data is a crucial step in maintaining a strong sender reputation and optimizing email deliverability. By understanding the reasons behind bounces, you can make informed adjustments to improve your email strategy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We\'re almost at the end of SQL30! Keep up the great work!</p>\r\n'),
