(2289, 719, '_description', '<p class=\"mb-0\">The NextMobile Marketing team is analyzing year-over-year click-through rates (CTRs) and they would like to understand email CTRs across different states in 2023. Your task is to create a query that calculates CTRs by analyzing email deliveries and clicks.</p>\r\n\r\n'),
(2290, 719, '__description', 'field_64dd19ca99237'),
(2291, 719, '_detail', 'In your final challenge, you\'ll focus on calculating email Click-Through Rates (CTRs). This metric measures recipient engagement by counting the number of clicks on the included links. The CTR is calculated by dividing the number of people who clicked on a link by the number of delivered emails, and then multiplying that ratio by 100 to get the email CTR percentage. If you\'re using Marketing Cloud Query Studio to run the query, ensure the calculated fields return a decimal and not an integer.'),
(2292, 719, '__detail', 'field_64e26bc8efb7b'),
(2293, 719, '_resources', '<p>For this task, you\'ll use these data extensions:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li><strong>NextMobile Users:</strong> Contains user-specific information, including their state.</li>\r\n  <li><strong>NextMobile Sent_2023:</strong> Records details of sent emails.</li>\r\n  <li><strong>NextMobile Click_2023:</strong> Stores click data.</li>\r\n  <li><strong>NextMobile Bounce_2023:</strong> Captures bounced emails.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Access the datasets for Sent, Click, and Bounce data extensions below:</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"d-grid gap-2 col-6\">\r\n  <a href=\"https://github.com/sabuhiy/mc30/blob/main/sql30/sql30_01_NextMobile%20Users.csv\" class=\"btn btn-success rounded-pill text-white\" target=\"_blank\">ð¾ NextMobile Users</a>\r\n  <a href=\"https://github.com/sabuhiy/mc30/blob/main/sql30/sql30_30_NextMobile%20Sent_2023.csv\" class=\"btn btn-success rounded-pill text-white\" target=\"_blank\">ð¾ NextMobile Sent_2023</a>\r\n  <a href=\"https://github.com/sabuhiy/mc30/blob/main/sql30/sql30_30_NextMobile%20Click_2023.csv\" class=\"btn btn-success rounded-pill text-white\" target=\"_blank\">ð¾ NextMobile Click_2023</a>\r\n  <a href=\"https://github.com/sabuhiy/mc30/blob/main/sql30/sql30_30_NextMobile%20Bounce_2023.csv\" class=\"btn btn-success rounded-pill text-white\" target=\"_blank\">ð¾ NextMobile Bounce_2023</a>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"fs-6 my-4\">Dataset Details</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The schemas (Dataset Details) for Sent, Click, and Bounce data extensions are identical, except that the Sent data extension does not include the IsUnique field. Refer to them below. Please note that these data extensions have fewer columns than the Marketing Cloud data views because I\'ve only included the relevant data columns for this challenge.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"table-responsive\">\r\n  <table class=\"table border-success\">\r\n    <thead>\r\n      <tr>\r\n        <th>Name</th>\r\n        <th>Data Type</th>\r\n        <th>Length</th>\r\n        <th>Primary Key</th>\r\n        <th>Nullable</th>\r\n      </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n      <tr>\r\n        <td>SubscriberKey</td>\r\n        <td>Text</td>\r\n        <td>50</td>\r\n        <td></td>\r\n        <td></td>\r\n      </tr>\r\n      <tr>\r\n        <td>EventDate</td>\r\n        <td>Date</td>\r\n        <td>254</td>\r\n        <td></td>\r\n        <td></td>\r\n      </tr>\r\n      <tr>\r\n        <td>IsUnique</td>\r\n        <td>Boolean</td>\r\n        <td></td>\r\n        <td></td>\r\n        <td></td>\r\n      </tr>\r\n      <tr>\r\n        <td>JobID</td>\r\n        <td>Text</td>\r\n        <td>50</td>\r\n        <td></td>\r\n        <td></td>\r\n      </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n  </table>\r\n</div>'),
