(222, 1, '2023-11-14 01:07:02', '2023-11-14 01:07:02', '<strong>Step 1: Navigate to the Specific Asset</strong>\n<ul>\n  <li>First, you need to decide on which marketing asset you want to add a completion action. This could be a form, a landing page, a custom redirect, a file, or an email.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<strong>Step 2: Access Settings/Options</strong>\n<ul>\n  <li>Once you\'re on the asset\'s main page, look for a section that might be labeled \"Completion Actions\"</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/completion-action-2-edited.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/completion-action-2-edited.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\n\n<strong>Step 3: Add Completion Action</strong>\n<ul>\n  <li>Click on the button or link that allows you to add a completion action. This might be labeled \"Add Completion Action,\" \"New Action,\" or something similar.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<strong>Step 4: Select Action Type</strong>\n<ul>\n  <li>A dropdown menu or list will appear, showing you all the available actions you can take on a prospect once the trigger event happens. Examples include \"Add to list,\" \"Assign to user,\" \"Adjust score,\" and so forth.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/completion-action-4-edited.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/completion-action-4-edited.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\n\n<strong>Step 5: Define Action Parameters</strong>\n<ul>\n  <li>Once you choose the desired action type, you\'ll need to specify the parameters for that action. For instance, if you chose \"Add to list,\" you\'ll need to select which list you want to add the prospect to.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/completion-action-5-edited.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/completion-action-5-edited.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\n\n<strong>Step 6: Conditional Completion Actions (if applicable)</strong>\n<ul>\n  <li>If you want your completion action to be conditional (meaning it only triggers under specific circumstances), you\'ll need to set those conditions. This might involve defining certain prospect criteria, like if they belong to a particular campaign or if they have a certain score.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/completion-action-6-edited.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/completion-action-6-edited.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\n\n<strong>Step 7: Save Your Changes</strong>\n<ul>\n  <li>After adding and defining your completion action(s), always make sure to save any changes you\'ve made to the asset.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<strong>Step 8: Test Your Completion Action</strong>\n<ul>\n  <li>It\'s a good practice to test completion actions to ensure they work as expected. You can do this by simulating a user interaction with the asset and then checking if the completion action triggers correctly.</li>\n</ul>\n', 'How to add a completion action to forms', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '121-autosave-v1', '', '', '2023-11-14 01:07:02', '2023-11-14 01:07:02', '', 121, 'https://marketingcloud30.com/?p=222', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(223, 1, '2023-11-14 01:14:16', '2023-11-14 01:14:16', '<strong>Step 1: Navigate to Page Actions</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>In your Account Engagement dashboard, go to <strong>Automations</strong> > <strong>Page Actions</strong>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/page-action-1.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/page-action-1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Step 2: Add New Page Action</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Click the <strong>+ Add Page Action</strong> button.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/page-action-2.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/page-action-2.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Step 3: Add Page Action Details</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li><strong>Name</strong>: Enter a descriptive name.</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Enter the Page URL</strong>: Enter the full URL of the page you want to track.</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Page Score (optional)</strong>: Adjust the page\'s score if you want it to be different from the default.</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Scoring Category (optional)</strong>: Choose a scoring category.</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Priority Page? (optional)</strong>: When enabled, this page will be highlighted separately in a prospect\'s activity.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/page-action-3.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/page-action-3.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Step 4: Add Completion Actions</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Select a completion action from the Action dropdown menu. Completion actions are triggered for known prospects after they visit this specific URL. For example, you can add a prospect to a Salesforce campaign when they visit the Page URL that you added in the previous step.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/page-action-4.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/page-action-4.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Step 5: Create the Page Action</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Click on <strong>Create page action</strong> button to publish your page action.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 'How to create a page action', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'how-to-create-a-page-action', '', '', '2023-11-14 01:14:16', '2023-11-14 01:14:16', '', 0, 'https://marketingcloud30.com/?post_type=guide&#038;p=223', 0, 'guide', '', 0),
