(653, 1, '2024-01-11 23:24:11', '2024-01-11 23:24:11', 'Marketing Cloud Account Engagement (Pardot) is the only platform in the B2B marketing automation space that offers free and unrestricted platform access*. This demo instance allows users to learn the ins and outs of the platform. It includes access to all platform capabilities and is ideal for practicing core functions and completing the MCAE30 30-day challenge.\r\n\r\nIn the following sections, you will find all the information you need to start using your MCAE instance.\r\n<div class=\"alert alert-primary rounded-3\" role=\"alert\">\r\n<div class=\"d-flex\">\r\n  <div class=\"p-1 flex-shrink-1\">ð¡</div>\r\n  <div class=\"p-1 w-100\">The content on this guide is based on Winderâ24 Salesforce release. While I try to keep the guide up-to-date, keep in mind that some screenshots in this guide may look like different in future releases.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"fs-3 mt-4 text-primary\">Demo Sign-up</h2>\r\nBefore you start with the provisioning, here are a few tips to prevent issues:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Ensure to do that with a browser session where you are completely logged out of any CRM/Account Engagement accounts</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Configure with a VALID email address</strong> to mitigate password reset and authentication issues.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Google &amp; O360Â <a href=\"https://thenextweb.com/google/2017/08/17/how-the-plus-sign-can-save-your-gmail-inbox-from-becoming-a-pit-of-doom/\">email accounts can use the + operator</a>Â to make multiple development accounts. This will allow you to create unique accounts and perform password resets.</li>\r\n 	<li>New Incognito window can be a great idea for that or see instructions for <a href=\"https://salesforce.quip.com/vr2RAbM33FHx#aRHACAUFLU4\">creating a separate browsing profile in chrome</a></li>\r\n 	<li>Another option is to useÂ chrome profiles, which may reduce issues with browser cookies and other log-in issues. Particularly valuable to consultants, which log-in to multiple client accounts:Â <a href=\"https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/2364824?co=GENIE.Platform%3DDesktop&amp;hl=en\">https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/2364824?co=GENIE.Platform%3DDesktop&amp;hl=en</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>â ï¸Â CAUTION: Do not connect this account to trailhead.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3 class=\"fs-4 mt-3\">Sign-up Steps</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Complete the sign-up form, making sure to use an active and monitored email address.</li>\r\n 	<li>Look for an email from <a href=\"mailto:developer@salesforce.com\">developer@salesforce.com</a> with a subject line âWelcome to Salesforce: Verify your accountâ</li>\r\n 	<li>After receiving the verification email, log in to the instance and set your password.</li>\r\n 	<li>Your objective is to reach the screen below:</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-1.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-1.png\" alt=\"Setup Screen\" /></a></div>\r\n<!-- Demo Configuration Instructions -->\r\n<h2 class=\"fs-3 mt-4 text-primary\">Demo Configuration Instructions</h2>\r\nThe setup process for the org in Production will be similar to setting up a a demo org, with the exception that certain settings and permissions have already been enabled in the demo instance. Please follow the summarized steps below. For more detailed information, you can refer to the Lightning App Enablement Guide document.\r\n\r\nâ±ï¸Â Estimated time to complete: 90 minutes if you configure everything (duration may vary depending on individual needs and experience with set-up)\r\n<h3 class=\"fs-4 mt-3\">Configuration Steps</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"#mcae-1\">Configure Business Unit and Choose your Admin</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"#mcae-2\">Install the Appexchange Package</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"#mcae-3\">Assign access to the Account Engagement Connected App</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"#mcae-4\">ApplyÂ the Account Engagement Connector User permission set</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"#mcae-5\">Update access to Lead and Contact fields for integration user</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"#mcae-6\">Enable Account Engagement Lightning App</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"#mcae-7\">Unpause the Salesforce connector</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"#mcae-8\">Enable Connected Campaigns (optional)</a></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<!-- 1. Configure Business Unit and Choose your Admin -->\r\n<h3 id=\"mcae-1\" class=\"fs-4 mt-3\">1. Configure Business Unit and Choose your Admin</h3>\r\nLogin to your demo Org fromÂ <a href=\"https://login.salesforce.com\">https://login.salesforce.com</a>Â and navigate to the Marketing Setup home screen. Next, click on <strong>Business Unit Setup</strong>Â under <strong>Setup for Marketing Automation</strong> section.\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-1a.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-1a.png\" alt=\"Marketing Setup\" /></a></div>\r\nName your business unit, for example, <code>MCAE30</code>, and then select the user you registered with under Setup Admin. ClickÂ Save.\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-2-1.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-2-1.png\" alt=\"Marketing Setup\" /></a></div>\r\nYou should receive a confirmation notification on the screen and then email confirming that your MCAE account is now ready:\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-2a.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-2a.png\" alt=\"Confirmation email\" /></a></div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"alert alert-warning rounded-3\" role=\"alert\">\r\n	<div class=\"d-flex\">\r\n		<div class=\"p-1 flex-shrink-1\">â ï¸</div>\r\n		<div class=\"p-1 w-100\">If you do not receive the email, please ensure you entered your email address correctly and check your spam folder. If you still do not see the email but can see that the Business Unit status is âEnabledâ, you may proceed with the instructions.\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-4.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-4.png\" alt=\"Business Unit\" /></a></div>\r\n<!-- 2. Install the Appexchange Package -->\r\n<h3 id=\"mcae-2\" class=\"fs-4 mt-3\">2. Install the Appexchange Package</h3>\r\nNavigate to the Marketing Cloud Account Engagement AppExchange Package Download page. In the Installation Links section, click on the link for Production Environments. Keep the Install for Admins option selected, and then click the Install button.\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-5.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-5.png\" alt=\"Business Unit\" /></a></div>\r\nCheck <code>Yes, grant access to these third-party web sites</code> and click Continue.\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-6.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-6.png\" alt=\"Business Unit\" /></a></div>\r\nWait until the installation completes or if a message appears indicating that the installation is taking a long time.\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-7.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-7.png\" alt=\"Business Unit\" /></a></div>\r\nIf this is the case pleaseÂ wait until an email confirming completion of installation arrives to you mailbox:\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-7a.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-7a.png\" alt=\"Business Unit\" /></a></div>\r\nClick DoneÂ button to close installation window.\r\n\r\n<!-- 3.Assign access to the Account Engagement Connected App -->\r\n<h3 id=\"mcae-3\" class=\"fs-4 mt-3\">3. Assign access to the Account Engagement Connected App</h3>\r\nThe Account Engagement Lightning app communicates with Account Engagement through a connected app, which is a feature in Salesforce for connecting applications. Access to the app is controlled by assigning profiles and/or permission sets.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>In Salesforce, go toÂ <strong>Setup &gt; Apps &gt; Connected Apps &gt; Manage Connected Apps</strong>.</li>\r\n 	<li>ClickÂ <code>b2bma_canvas</code>.</li>\r\n 	<li>Click <strong>Manage Profiles</strong></li>\r\n 	<li>Verify thatÂ <strong>System Administrator</strong>Â profile is selected, if it is not ensure to select it and save the assignment.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-8.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-8.png\" alt=\"Business Unit\" /></a></div>\r\n<!-- 4. ApplyÂ the Account Engagement Connector User permission set -->\r\n<h3 id=\"mcae-4\" class=\"fs-4 mt-3\">4. ApplyÂ the Account Engagement Connector User permission set</h3>\r\nAssign theÂ <strong><code>CRM User</code></strong>,Â <strong><code>Sales Cloud User</code></strong>, orÂ <code>**Service Cloud User**</code>Â permission set to yourself. For the demo instance, weâll be usingÂ <strong><code>CRM User</code></strong>Â permission set. Depending on your Salesforce org, youâll see one or all of these permission sets available by default.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>In Salesforce, go toÂ <strong>Setup &gt; Users &gt; Permission Sets</strong>.</li>\r\n 	<li>ClickÂ <strong>CRM User</strong></li>\r\n 	<li>Click <strong>Manage Assignments</strong>.</li>\r\n 	<li>Click <strong>Add Assignments</strong>.</li>\r\n 	<li>Select your admin user and click <strong>Assign</strong> and then <strong>Done</strong>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-9.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-9.png\" alt=\"Business Unit\" /></a></div>\r\n<!-- 5. Update access to Lead and Contact fields for integration user -->\r\n<h3 id=\"mcae-5\" class=\"fs-4 mt-3\">5. Update access to Lead and Contact fields for integration user</h3>\r\nDefault field level security does not allow access to <strong>Email Opt Out</strong>Â field for <strong>Lead</strong> and <strong>Contact</strong>Â objects to the integration user configured in our demo account.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>While inÂ <strong>Setup</strong>Â underÂ <strong>Objects and Fields</strong>Â click onÂ <strong>Object Manager</strong></li>\r\n 	<li>Locate and click onÂ <strong>Contact</strong>Â object record</li>\r\n 	<li>Click on <strong>Fields &amp; Relationships</strong></li>\r\n 	<li>Locate and click on <strong>Email Opt Out</strong>Â field</li>\r\n 	<li>Click on <strong>Set Field-Level Security</strong>Â button</li>\r\n 	<li>In the <strong>Visible</strong>Â column select checkbox for <strong>B2BMA Integration User</strong> and <strong>System Administrator</strong>Â profiles and click <strong>Save</strong></li>\r\n 	<li>Return to <strong>Object Manager</strong>Â and for theÂ <strong>Lead</strong>Â object. (<em><strong>Repeat the same steps the Lead Object</strong></em>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-10.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-10.png\" alt=\"Business Unit\" /></a></div>\r\nReturn to the <strong><span class=\"notion-enable-hover\" data-token-index=\"1\">Object Manager</span></strong>Â and repeat steps 3-6 for <strong><span class=\"notion-enable-hover\" data-token-index=\"3\">Lead</span></strong>Â object.<!-- notionvc: a365070c-bb62-45b2-9acf-b842cd1f7489 -->\r\n\r\n<!-- 6. Enable Account Engagement Lightning App -->\r\n<h3 id=\"mcae-6\" class=\"fs-4 mt-3\">6.Enable Account Engagement Lightning App</h3>\r\nNavigate toÂ <span class=\"notion-enable-hover\" data-token-index=\"1\"><strong>Marketing Setup &gt; Setup Assistant</strong>Â </span>and in the step 3 toggle the switch to enable state:<!-- notionvc: 165a8f61-e3ca-4d4c-a367-a7f87ca808b6 -->\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-11.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-11.png\" alt=\"Business Unit\" /></a></div>\r\n<!-- 7. Unpause the Salesforce connector -->\r\n<h3 id=\"mcae-7\" class=\"fs-4 mt-3\">7. Unpause the Salesforce connector</h3>\r\nVersion 2 of Salesforce-Account Engagement connector is created in a paused state. An Account Engagement admin must configure the connector and unpause it to begin syncing data between Account Engagement and CRM.Â  If it is inÂ <span class=\"notion-enable-hover\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-token-index=\"1\">Verification in Progress</span>Â status instead of <strong><span class=\"notion-enable-hover\" data-token-index=\"3\">Paused status</span></strong>, please <span class=\"notion-enable-hover\" data-token-index=\"5\">wait</span>Â up to an hour to complete verification, then return to unpause it. <!-- notionvc: 503e52e1-b158-4864-a971-531812d9e195 -->\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-12.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-12.png\" alt=\"Business Unit\" /></a></div>\r\nClick the gear icon next to theÂ <strong><span class=\"notion-enable-hover\" data-token-index=\"1\">Salesforce Connector</span></strong>, and select <strong><span class=\"notion-enable-hover\" data-token-index=\"3\">Resume Sync</span></strong>.<!-- notionvc: f27842b3-c4d1-4fd1-ad4f-71d1d7ab61c5 -->\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-13.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-13.png\" alt=\"Business Unit\" /></a></div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"alert alert-warning rounded-3\" role=\"alert\">\r\n<div class=\"d-flex\">\r\n<div class=\"p-1 flex-shrink-1\">â ï¸</div>\r\n<div class=\"p-1 w-100\">If you have been waiting for over 1 hour for your connector to verify, please refer to the troubleshooting links provided at the end of this page for more information.\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<!-- 8. Enable Connected Campaigns (optional) -->\r\n<h3 id=\"mcae-8\" class=\"fs-4 mt-3\">8. Enable Connected Campaigns (optional)</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Go to Account Engagement Settings and click on Connectors. Then, select <strong>Edit Settings</strong> for the <a href=\"http://salesforce.com/\">Salesforce.com</a> connector.</li>\r\n 	<li>Navigate to the <strong>Campaigns</strong> tab.</li>\r\n 	<li>Choose the Salesforce campaign record types that you want marketers to connect to in Salesforce campaigns. The master record type is the default type applied to all records before any custom record types are created.</li>\r\n 	<li>Check Use Salesforce to manage all campaigns.</li>\r\n 	<li>Click Save.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-14.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-14.png\" alt=\"Business Unit\" /></a></div>\r\nNext, you need to create two new campaigns. This step is necessary because each asset needs to be attached to a campaign. You can name your two new campaigns as \"Created from Salesforce\" and \"Account Engagement Evergreen\".\r\n\r\nTo create the campaigns, follow these steps:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Navigate to the Campaigns tab and click on <strong>New</strong>.</li>\r\n 	<li>Provide a name for each campaign.</li>\r\n 	<li>Ensure that the <strong>Active</strong> box is checked.</li>\r\n 	<li>Select <strong>Other</strong> as the Campaign Type.</li>\r\n 	<li>Click on <strong>Save</strong> and wait for 4-5 minutes for the campaigns to become visible in Account Engagement.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-15.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-15.png\" alt=\"Business Unit\" /></a></div>\r\n<h2 class=\"fs-3 mt-4 text-primary\">Troubleshooting</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>I am able to access the Account Engagement Lightning App, but the screen shows a loading icon. Please refer to this <a href=\"https://help.salesforce.com/s/articleView?language=en_US&amp;id=000380206&amp;type=1\">Help Article</a> for assistance.</li>\r\n 	<li>The Salesforce-Account Engagement Connector is stuck at \'Verification in Progress\'. For more information, please check this <a href=\"https://help.salesforce.com/s/articleView?language=en_US&amp;id=000380484&amp;type=1\">Help Article</a>.</li>\r\n 	<li>When using the Account Engagement Lightning App, I cannot see all the tabs in the top navigation bar. Please consult this <a href=\"https://help.salesforce.com/s/articleView?id=000380484&amp;type=1\">Help Article</a> for guidance.</li>\r\n 	<li>I am unable to add a new campaign in Salesforce following the instructions provided above. Please refer to this <a href=\"https://help.salesforce.com/s/articleView?id=000380794&amp;type=1\">Help Article</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<small>Disclaimer: The content on this page is based on an earlier version of the deployment guide created by Lindsey Mark.</small>', 'How to deploy Marketing Cloud Account Engagement (Pardot) Demo Instance', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '567-revision-v1', '', '', '2024-01-11 23:24:11', '2024-01-11 23:24:11', '', 567, 'https://marketingcloud30.com/?p=653', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(654, 1, '2024-01-12 06:30:58', '2024-01-12 06:30:58', 'Marketing Cloud Account Engagement (Pardot) is the only platform in the B2B marketing automation space that offers free and unrestricted platform access*. This demo instance allows users to learn the ins and outs of the platform. It includes access to all platform capabilities and is ideal for practicing core functions and completing the MCAE30 30-day challenge.\r\n\r\nIn the following sections, you will find all the information you need to start using your MCAE instance.\r\n<div class=\"alert alert-primary rounded-3\" role=\"alert\">\r\n<div class=\"d-flex\">\r\n  <div class=\"p-1 flex-shrink-1\">ð¡</div>\r\n  <div class=\"p-1 w-100\">The content on this guide is based on Winderâ24 Salesforce release. While I try to keep the guide up-to-date, keep in mind that some screenshots in this guide may look like different in future releases.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"fs-3 mt-4 text-primary\">Demo Sign-up</h2>\r\nBefore you start with the provisioning, here are a few tips to prevent issues:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Ensure to do that with a browser session where you are completely logged out of any CRM/Account Engagement accounts</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Configure with a VALID email address</strong> to mitigate password reset and authentication issues.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Google &amp; O360Â <a href=\"https://thenextweb.com/google/2017/08/17/how-the-plus-sign-can-save-your-gmail-inbox-from-becoming-a-pit-of-doom/\">email accounts can use the + operator</a>Â to make multiple development accounts. This will allow you to create unique accounts and perform password resets.</li>\r\n 	<li>New Incognito window can be a great idea for that or see instructions for <a href=\"https://salesforce.quip.com/vr2RAbM33FHx#aRHACAUFLU4\">creating a separate browsing profile in chrome</a></li>\r\n 	<li>Another option is to useÂ chrome profiles, which may reduce issues with browser cookies and other log-in issues. Particularly valuable to consultants, which log-in to multiple client accounts:Â <a href=\"https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/2364824?co=GENIE.Platform%3DDesktop&amp;hl=en\">https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/2364824?co=GENIE.Platform%3DDesktop&amp;hl=en</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>â ï¸Â CAUTION: Do not connect this account to trailhead.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3 class=\"fs-4 mt-3\">Sign-up Steps</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Complete the <a href=\"https://trailhead.salesforce.com/promo/orgs/pardot-de\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">sign-up form</a>, making sure to use an active and monitored email address.</li>\r\n 	<li>Look for an email from <a href=\"mailto:developer@salesforce.com\">developer@salesforce.com</a> with a subject line âWelcome to Salesforce: Verify your accountâ</li>\r\n 	<li>After receiving the verification email, log in to the instance and set your password.</li>\r\n 	<li>Your objective is to reach the screen below:</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-1.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-1.png\" alt=\"Setup Screen\" /></a></div>\r\n<!-- Demo Configuration Instructions -->\r\n<h2 class=\"fs-3 mt-4 text-primary\">Demo Configuration Instructions</h2>\r\nThe setup process for the org in Production will be similar to setting up a a demo org, with the exception that certain settings and permissions have already been enabled in the demo instance. Please follow the summarized steps below. For more detailed information, you can refer to the Lightning App Enablement Guide document.\r\n\r\nâ±ï¸Â Estimated time to complete: 90 minutes if you configure everything (duration may vary depending on individual needs and experience with set-up)\r\n<h3 class=\"fs-4 mt-3\">Configuration Steps</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"#mcae-1\">Configure Business Unit and Choose your Admin</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"#mcae-2\">Install the Appexchange Package</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"#mcae-3\">Assign access to the Account Engagement Connected App</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"#mcae-4\">ApplyÂ the Account Engagement Connector User permission set</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"#mcae-5\">Update access to Lead and Contact fields for integration user</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"#mcae-6\">Enable Account Engagement Lightning App</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"#mcae-7\">Unpause the Salesforce connector</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"#mcae-8\">Enable Connected Campaigns (optional)</a></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<!-- 1. Configure Business Unit and Choose your Admin -->\r\n<h3 id=\"mcae-1\" class=\"fs-4 mt-3\">1. Configure Business Unit and Choose your Admin</h3>\r\nLogin to your demo Org fromÂ <a href=\"https://login.salesforce.com\">https://login.salesforce.com</a>Â and navigate to the Marketing Setup home screen. Next, click on <strong>Business Unit Setup</strong>Â under <strong>Setup for Marketing Automation</strong> section.\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-1a.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-1a.png\" alt=\"Marketing Setup\" /></a></div>\r\nName your business unit, for example, <code>MCAE30</code>, and then select the user you registered with under Setup Admin. ClickÂ Save.\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-2-1.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-2-1.png\" alt=\"Marketing Setup\" /></a></div>\r\nYou should receive a confirmation notification on the screen and then email confirming that your MCAE account is now ready:\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-2a.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-2a.png\" alt=\"Confirmation email\" /></a></div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"alert alert-warning rounded-3\" role=\"alert\">\r\n	<div class=\"d-flex\">\r\n		<div class=\"p-1 flex-shrink-1\">â ï¸</div>\r\n		<div class=\"p-1 w-100\">If you do not receive the email, please ensure you entered your email address correctly and check your spam folder. If you still do not see the email but can see that the Business Unit status is âEnabledâ, you may proceed with the instructions.\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-4.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-4.png\" alt=\"Business Unit\" /></a></div>\r\n<!-- 2. Install the Appexchange Package -->\r\n<h3 id=\"mcae-2\" class=\"fs-4 mt-3\">2. Install the Appexchange Package</h3>\r\nNavigate to the Marketing Cloud Account Engagement AppExchange Package Download page. In the Installation Links section, click on the link for Production Environments. Keep the Install for Admins option selected, and then click the Install button.\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-5.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-5.png\" alt=\"Business Unit\" /></a></div>\r\nCheck <code>Yes, grant access to these third-party web sites</code> and click Continue.\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-6.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-6.png\" alt=\"Business Unit\" /></a></div>\r\nWait until the installation completes or if a message appears indicating that the installation is taking a long time.\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-7.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-7.png\" alt=\"Business Unit\" /></a></div>\r\nIf this is the case pleaseÂ wait until an email confirming completion of installation arrives to you mailbox:\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-7a.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-7a.png\" alt=\"Business Unit\" /></a></div>\r\nClick DoneÂ button to close installation window.\r\n\r\n<!-- 3.Assign access to the Account Engagement Connected App -->\r\n<h3 id=\"mcae-3\" class=\"fs-4 mt-3\">3. Assign access to the Account Engagement Connected App</h3>\r\nThe Account Engagement Lightning app communicates with Account Engagement through a connected app, which is a feature in Salesforce for connecting applications. Access to the app is controlled by assigning profiles and/or permission sets.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>In Salesforce, go toÂ <strong>Setup &gt; Apps &gt; Connected Apps &gt; Manage Connected Apps</strong>.</li>\r\n 	<li>ClickÂ <code>b2bma_canvas</code>.</li>\r\n 	<li>Click <strong>Manage Profiles</strong></li>\r\n 	<li>Verify thatÂ <strong>System Administrator</strong>Â profile is selected, if it is not ensure to select it and save the assignment.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-8.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-8.png\" alt=\"Business Unit\" /></a></div>\r\n<!-- 4. ApplyÂ the Account Engagement Connector User permission set -->\r\n<h3 id=\"mcae-4\" class=\"fs-4 mt-3\">4. ApplyÂ the Account Engagement Connector User permission set</h3>\r\nAssign theÂ <strong><code>CRM User</code></strong>,Â <strong><code>Sales Cloud User</code></strong>, orÂ <code>**Service Cloud User**</code>Â permission set to yourself. For the demo instance, weâll be usingÂ <strong><code>CRM User</code></strong>Â permission set. Depending on your Salesforce org, youâll see one or all of these permission sets available by default.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>In Salesforce, go toÂ <strong>Setup &gt; Users &gt; Permission Sets</strong>.</li>\r\n 	<li>ClickÂ <strong>CRM User</strong></li>\r\n 	<li>Click <strong>Manage Assignments</strong>.</li>\r\n 	<li>Click <strong>Add Assignments</strong>.</li>\r\n 	<li>Select your admin user and click <strong>Assign</strong> and then <strong>Done</strong>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-9.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-9.png\" alt=\"Business Unit\" /></a></div>\r\n<!-- 5. Update access to Lead and Contact fields for integration user -->\r\n<h3 id=\"mcae-5\" class=\"fs-4 mt-3\">5. Update access to Lead and Contact fields for integration user</h3>\r\nDefault field level security does not allow access to <strong>Email Opt Out</strong>Â field for <strong>Lead</strong> and <strong>Contact</strong>Â objects to the integration user configured in our demo account.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>While inÂ <strong>Setup</strong>Â underÂ <strong>Objects and Fields</strong>Â click onÂ <strong>Object Manager</strong></li>\r\n 	<li>Locate and click onÂ <strong>Contact</strong>Â object record</li>\r\n 	<li>Click on <strong>Fields &amp; Relationships</strong></li>\r\n 	<li>Locate and click on <strong>Email Opt Out</strong>Â field</li>\r\n 	<li>Click on <strong>Set Field-Level Security</strong>Â button</li>\r\n 	<li>In the <strong>Visible</strong>Â column select checkbox for <strong>B2BMA Integration User</strong> and <strong>System Administrator</strong>Â profiles and click <strong>Save</strong></li>\r\n 	<li>Return to <strong>Object Manager</strong>Â and for theÂ <strong>Lead</strong>Â object. (<em><strong>Repeat the same steps the Lead Object</strong></em>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-10.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-10.png\" alt=\"Business Unit\" /></a></div>\r\nReturn to the <strong><span class=\"notion-enable-hover\" data-token-index=\"1\">Object Manager</span></strong>Â and repeat steps 3-6 for <strong><span class=\"notion-enable-hover\" data-token-index=\"3\">Lead</span></strong>Â object.<!-- notionvc: a365070c-bb62-45b2-9acf-b842cd1f7489 -->\r\n\r\n<!-- 6. Enable Account Engagement Lightning App -->\r\n<h3 id=\"mcae-6\" class=\"fs-4 mt-3\">6.Enable Account Engagement Lightning App</h3>\r\nNavigate toÂ <span class=\"notion-enable-hover\" data-token-index=\"1\"><strong>Marketing Setup &gt; Setup Assistant</strong>Â </span>and in the step 3 toggle the switch to enable state:<!-- notionvc: 165a8f61-e3ca-4d4c-a367-a7f87ca808b6 -->\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-11.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-11.png\" alt=\"Business Unit\" /></a></div>\r\n<!-- 7. Unpause the Salesforce connector -->\r\n<h3 id=\"mcae-7\" class=\"fs-4 mt-3\">7. Unpause the Salesforce connector</h3>\r\nVersion 2 of Salesforce-Account Engagement connector is created in a paused state. An Account Engagement admin must configure the connector and unpause it to begin syncing data between Account Engagement and CRM.Â  If it is inÂ <span class=\"notion-enable-hover\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-token-index=\"1\">Verification in Progress</span>Â status instead of <strong><span class=\"notion-enable-hover\" data-token-index=\"3\">Paused status</span></strong>, please <span class=\"notion-enable-hover\" data-token-index=\"5\">wait</span>Â up to an hour to complete verification, then return to unpause it. <!-- notionvc: 503e52e1-b158-4864-a971-531812d9e195 -->\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-12.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-12.png\" alt=\"Business Unit\" /></a></div>\r\nClick the gear icon next to theÂ <strong><span class=\"notion-enable-hover\" data-token-index=\"1\">Salesforce Connector</span></strong>, and select <strong><span class=\"notion-enable-hover\" data-token-index=\"3\">Resume Sync</span></strong>.<!-- notionvc: f27842b3-c4d1-4fd1-ad4f-71d1d7ab61c5 -->\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-13.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-13.png\" alt=\"Business Unit\" /></a></div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"alert alert-warning rounded-3\" role=\"alert\">\r\n<div class=\"d-flex\">\r\n<div class=\"p-1 flex-shrink-1\">â ï¸</div>\r\n<div class=\"p-1 w-100\">If you have been waiting for over 1 hour for your connector to verify, please refer to the troubleshooting links provided at the end of this page for more information.\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<!-- 8. Enable Connected Campaigns (optional) -->\r\n<h3 id=\"mcae-8\" class=\"fs-4 mt-3\">8. Enable Connected Campaigns (optional)</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Go to Account Engagement Settings and click on Connectors. Then, select <strong>Edit Settings</strong> for the <a href=\"http://salesforce.com/\">Salesforce.com</a> connector.</li>\r\n 	<li>Navigate to the <strong>Campaigns</strong> tab.</li>\r\n 	<li>Choose the Salesforce campaign record types that you want marketers to connect to in Salesforce campaigns. The master record type is the default type applied to all records before any custom record types are created.</li>\r\n 	<li>Check Use Salesforce to manage all campaigns.</li>\r\n 	<li>Click Save.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-14.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-14.png\" alt=\"Business Unit\" /></a></div>\r\nNext, you need to create two new campaigns. This step is necessary because each asset needs to be attached to a campaign. You can name your two new campaigns as \"Created from Salesforce\" and \"Account Engagement Evergreen\".\r\n\r\nTo create the campaigns, follow these steps:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Navigate to the Campaigns tab and click on <strong>New</strong>.</li>\r\n 	<li>Provide a name for each campaign.</li>\r\n 	<li>Ensure that the <strong>Active</strong> box is checked.</li>\r\n 	<li>Select <strong>Other</strong> as the Campaign Type.</li>\r\n 	<li>Click on <strong>Save</strong> and wait for 4-5 minutes for the campaigns to become visible in Account Engagement.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-15.png\" data-fslightbox=\"\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/setup-15.png\" alt=\"Business Unit\" /></a></div>\r\n<h2 class=\"fs-3 mt-4 text-primary\">Troubleshooting</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>I am able to access the Account Engagement Lightning App, but the screen shows a loading icon. Please refer to this <a href=\"https://help.salesforce.com/s/articleView?language=en_US&amp;id=000380206&amp;type=1\">Help Article</a> for assistance.</li>\r\n 	<li>The Salesforce-Account Engagement Connector is stuck at \'Verification in Progress\'. For more information, please check this <a href=\"https://help.salesforce.com/s/articleView?language=en_US&amp;id=000380484&amp;type=1\">Help Article</a>.</li>\r\n 	<li>When using the Account Engagement Lightning App, I cannot see all the tabs in the top navigation bar. Please consult this <a href=\"https://help.salesforce.com/s/articleView?id=000380484&amp;type=1\">Help Article</a> for guidance.</li>\r\n 	<li>I am unable to add a new campaign in Salesforce following the instructions provided above. Please refer to this <a href=\"https://help.salesforce.com/s/articleView?id=000380794&amp;type=1\">Help Article</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<small>Disclaimer: The content on this page is based on an earlier version of the deployment guide created by Lindsey Mark.</small>', 'How to deploy Marketing Cloud Account Engagement (Pardot) Demo Instance', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '567-revision-v1', '', '', '2024-01-12 06:30:58', '2024-01-12 06:30:58', '', 567, 'https://marketingcloud30.com/?p=654', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
